<p><em>Global leader in digital skills partners with Calgary Economic Development t</em>o <em>offer additional online courses in data, design, development, digital marketing, product, and business.&nbsp;</em></p>



<p>Calgary, AB &#8212; BrainStation, the global leader in digital skills training, has partnered with the Calgary Economic Development to provide additional courses in data, design, development, digital marketing, product, and business for professionals in Alberta. <br><br>The partnership is in support of the <a href="https://brainstation.mxdogwood.com/599ccdbf2522fc44a8ef9f5c/l/uCFb5bk46ND2dOa4q?messageId=42PdY645rVG6flZNY&amp;rn=ikmZs9WaDBCbhNlI&amp;re=gIvlmLu9Wa0FGdz5WahJnYAlmZs9WajNnI&amp;sc=false" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Alberta Jobs Now</a> program, a federal-provincial partnership that aims to provide up to $370 million to help Albertans and businesses in the province prepare for the future of work.<br><br>“We’re very proud to be offering additional online learning opportunities to support Alberta’s recovery and to help Albertans gain the skills they need in today’s job market,” said Kyle Treleaven, Vice President and General Manager of BrainStation. “With businesses in the province reopening and growing their workforces, and organizations like RBC announcing expansions in the province, there’s never been a better time for professionals to develop new digital skills,” he said.  </p>



